# Applies to the FRONTEND image build only (context = repo root, file =
# frontend/Dockerfile), which needs frontend/ + docs-content/ as siblings. The
# backend image builds from its own ./backend context (see backend/.dockerignore).
# Keeps the context lean and secret-free; the Dockerfile COPYs only the dirs it needs.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/build
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.log
**/coverage
.git
.claude
wiki
deploy/xrdp-test
